The first episode of ''The Flash'' was watched by 4.8 million viewers and had a 1.9 18–49 demographic rating, making it The CW's most watched and highest rated series premiere since ''[[The_Vampire_Diaries|The Vampire Diaries]]'' in 2009. It also became The CW's second-most watched series premiere ever, behind ''[[90210_(TV_series)|90210]]'', and the third-highest rated in the 18–49 demographic.<ref name="S1PremiereRatings">{{cite news|url=http://tvline.com/2014/10/08/the-flash-premiere-ratings/ |title=Ratings: The Flash Hits the Ground Running, CW's Best Debut in 5 Years; ABC Sitcoms Tumble, POI Slips |last=Mitovich |first=Matt Webb |work=TVLine |date=2014-10-08 |access-date=2014-10-12 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141012124431/http://tvline.com/2014/10/08/the-flash-premiere-ratings/ |archive-date=2014-10-12 |language=en-US}}</ref> Factoring Live + 7 day ratings, the pilot was watched by a total of 6.8 million viewers, becoming The CW's most-watched telecast and the highest-rated premiere among men 18–34 (2.5 rating). It broke the previous record for the most-watched telecast held by the [[America's_Next_Top_Model_(cycle_8)|cycle 8 finale of ''America's Next Top Model'']] in 2007 (6.69 million). Additionally, across all platforms, including initiated streams on digital platforms and total unduplicated viewers on-air over two airings the week of October 7, 2014, the premiere was seen more than 13 million times.<ref name="S1PremiereLive7">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/the-flash-premiere-stands-as-most-watched-cw-telecast-ever-1201340371/ |title=The Flash’ Premiere Stands as Most-Watched CW Telecast Ever |last=Kissell |first=Rick |work=[[Variety_(magazine)|Variety]] |date=2014-10-27 |access-date=2014-10-27 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141029235623/http://variety.com/2014/tv/news/the-flash-premiere-stands-as-most-watched-cw-telecast-ever-1201340371/ |archive-date=2014-10-29 |language=en-US}}</ref>

The Canadian premiere was watched by 3.11 million viewers, making it the most-watched broadcast that night and the second for that week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://assets.numeris.ca/Downloads/October%206-October%2012,%202014%20(National).pdf |title=Top 30 Programs (October 6–12, 2014) |work=Numeris |date=2014-10-21 |access-date=2015-02-20 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022153930/http://assets.numeris.ca/Downloads/October%206-October%2012%2C%202014%20%28National%29.pdf |archive-date=2014-10-22 |language=en-US}}</ref> In the United Kingdom, the premiere was the fourth highest-rated broadcast of the week and the eleventh of that month, with 1.53 million viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/weekly-top-30? |title=Weekly Top 30 |publisher=Broadcasters' Audience Research Board |access-date=2015-02-20 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5wSLX6Azh?url=http://www.barb.co.uk/report/weeklyTopProgrammesOverview |archive-date=2011-02-13 }} Note: The ratings must be searched for.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/monthly-top-30? |title=Monthly Top 30 |publisher=Broadcasters' Audience Research Board |access-date=2015-02-20 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150220204506/http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/monthly-top-30 |archive-date=2015-02-20 }} Note: The ratings must be searched for.</ref> The timeshifted version got 82,000 viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/weekly-top-10? |title=Weekly Top 10 |publisher=Broadcasters' Audience Research Board |access-date=2015-02-20 |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140718204656/http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/weekly-top-10 |archive-date=2014-07-18 }} Note: The ratings must be searched for.</ref> The premiere in Australia was the most-watched broadcast on pay television, with 129,000 viewers tuning in.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2014/12/wednesday-3-december-2014.html |title=Wednesday 3 December 2014 |date=2014-12-04 |last=Knox |first=David |website=TV Tonight |access-date=2015-02-20 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150220204907/http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2014/12/wednesday-3-december-2014.html |archive-date=2015-02-20 |language=en-US}}</ref>

The first season finished as the 118th ranked show, with an average viewership of 4.62 million,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/05/2014-15-full-tv-season-ratings-shows-rankings-1201431167/ |title=2014-15 Full TV Season Ratings: Rankings For All Shows - Deadline |author=Lisa de Moraes |website=Deadline Hollywood |access-date=2016-04-01 |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522054915/http://deadline.com/2015/05/2014-15-full-tv-season-ratings-shows-rankings-1201431167/ |archive-date=2015-05-22 |language=en-US}}</ref> helping to deliver The CW's most watched season in seven years.<ref name="CW2014-15">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/network-press-releases/the-cw-delivers-its-most-watched-season-in-7-years/403500/|title=The CW Delivers its Most Watched Season in 7 Years|last=Baron|first=Steve|work=TV by the Numbers|date=2015-05-13|access-date=2016-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170605153534/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/network-press-releases/the-cw-delivers-its-most-watched-season-in-7-years/403500/|archive-date=2017-06-05|dead-url=yes|language=en-US}}</ref> ''The Flash'' finished the season as the most watched series ever on The CW with 5.85 million viewers, and also the highest rated series among men 18–49 (2.8 rating) and men 18+ ever on the network.<ref name="CW2014-15"/>

=== Critical response ===
Season 1 of ''The Flash'' received generally positive reviews from critics. The [[review_aggregator|review aggregator]] website [[Rotten_Tomatoes|Rotten Tomatoes]] reported a 92% approval rating with an average rating of 7.75/10 based on 63 reviews. The website's consensus reads, "''The Flash'' benefits from its purposefully light atmosphere, making it a superhero show uniquely geared toward genre fans as well as novices."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/flash/s01/ |title=THE FLASH: SEASON 1 |website=Rotten Tomatoes |access-date=2020-02-26 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141020211822/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/flash/s01/ |archive-date=2014-10-20 |language=en-US}}</ref> [[Metacritic|Metacritic]], which uses a weighted average, assigned a score of 73 out of 100, based on 27 reviews, indicating "generally favorable reviews".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/the-flash-2014 |title=The Flash (2014) : Season 1 |publisher=CBS |work=Metacritic |access-date=2014-10-21 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022234643/http://www.metacritic.com/tv/the-flash-2014 |archive-date=2014-10-22 |language=en-US}}</ref>

[[IGN|IGN]]'s Eric Goldman and Joshua Yehl praised the show's premise and cast after viewing a press screening copy of the pilot. Goldman and Yehl favorably compared it to ''Arrow'', stating that ''The Flash'' progresses with a confidence that ''Arrow'' did not get until later in the series.<ref name="IGNPilotThoughts">{{cite av media|url=https://www.ign.com/videos/2014/06/27/the-flash-first-reaction-to-the-pilot-ign-conversation |title=The Flash – First Reaction to the Pilot |publisher=IGN |date=2014-06-26 |access-date=2014-06-28 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627051405/http://www.ign.com/videos/2014/06/27/the-flash-first-reaction-to-the-pilot-ign-conversation |archive-date=2014-06-27 |language=en-US}}</ref> Reviews for the series became increasingly positive as the season progressed, with the finale receiving critical acclaim. 

Noel Murray of [[The_A.V._Club|The A.V. Club]] gave the season a B+ overall, giving praise to the pacing of the plot, the performances of the cast and the special effects, and also pointing out the series' boldness to embrace its comic book influences, something that conventional superhero shows tend not to do.<ref name="AVClubS1">{{cite web|url=https://www.avclub.com/review/flashs-first-season-brought-fun-back-live-action-s-219446 |last=Murray |first=Noel |title=The Flash’s first season brought the fun back to live-action superheroes |publisher=The Onion A.V. Club |date=2015-05-19 |access-date=2015-06-12 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612101405/http://www.avclub.com/review/flashs-first-season-brought-fun-back-live-action-s-219446 |archive-date=2015-06-12 |language=en-US}}</ref> Weekly episode reviewer Scott Von Doviak gave consistently high ratings to the season and awarded the season finale a perfect A grade, calling the episode "richly satisfying" and also commending the show for "[capturing] the essence of its source material in a fun, light-on-its-feet way that few other comic book adaptations have managed." He also gave high praise to the emotional value and performances of the cast, as well as the cliffhanger and multiple easter eggs found in the episode.<ref name="S1FinaleAVClub">{{cite web|url=https://www.avclub.com/tvclub/flash-fast-enough-219671 |title=The Flash: "Fast Enough" |last=Von Doviak |first=Scott |publisher=The Onion A.V. Club |date=2015-05-19 |access-date=2015-06-12 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150614214116/http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/flash-fast-enough-219671 |archive-date=2015-06-14 |language=en-US}}</ref>
