''The Flash'' was included on multiple Best/Top TV Shows of 2014 lists, ranking on ''[[NPR|NPR]]'' and ''[[Omaha_World-Herald|Omaha World-Herald]]''{{'}}s (7th), and ''[[Film_School_Rejects|Film School Rejects]]''{{'}} (10th).<ref>{{cite web |title=Best of 2014: Television Critic Top Ten Lists |work=Metacritic |url=https://www.metacritic.com/feature/tv-critics-pick-10-best-tv-shows-of-2014 |date=2014-12-09 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151106015332/http://www.metacritic.com/feature/tv-critics-pick-10-best-tv-shows-of-2014 |archive-date=2015-11-06|language=en-US}}</ref> In its first season, ''The Flash'' was nominated for 35 awards, including an [[Primetime_Emmy_Awards|Emmy]] nomination for [[Primetime_Emmy_Award_for_Outstanding_Special_Visual_Effects|Outstanding Special Visual Effects]] for the episode "Grodd Lives",<ref name="2015EmmyNom"/> and winning nine. The show was nominated for four [[Saturn_Awards|Saturn Awards]], winning [[Saturn_Award_for_Best_Superhero_Adaptation_Television_Series|Best Superhero Adaption Television Series]] and Wentworth Miller winning for [[Saturn_Award_for_Best_Guest_Starring_Role_on_Television|Best Guest Star on Television]].<ref name="41st Saturn Awards" /> Gustin was honored with the Breakthrough Performance Saturn Award at the ceremony for his electrifying performance as Barry Allen/The Flash.<ref name="GrantSaturn"/> The series received eight [[Leo_Awards|Leo Awards]] nominations, including Best Dramatic Series and winning Best Visual Effects in a Dramatic Series for the episode "Going Rogue".<ref name="2015 Leo Awards" /> It also won the [[People's_Choice_Awards|People's Choice Award]] for "Favorite New TV Drama" for the 2014–15 season.<ref name="PeopleChoiceAwards"/> ''[[The_Atlantic|The Atlantic]]'' named the season finale, "Fast Enough" one of the best television episodes of 2015.<ref name="AtlanticBest2015">{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2015/12/the-best-television-episodes-of-2015/421053/ |title=The Best Television Episodes of 2015 |last=Sims |first=David |work=[[The_Atlantic|The Atlantic]] |date=2015-12-18 |access-date=2015-12-20 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6duQkBQ7E?url=http://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2015/12/the-best-television-episodes-of-2015/421053/ |archive-date=2015-12-20 |dead-url=no |language=en-US}}</ref>
